SIMPLE: ducat
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ducat
<hw>Duc"at</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>ducat</ets>,
It. <ets>ducato</ets>, LL. <ets>ducatus</ets>, fr. <ets>dux</ets> leader
or commander. See <er>Duke</er>.]</ety> <def>A coin, either of gold or
silver, of several countries in Europe; originally, one struck in the
dominions of a duke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The gold ducat is generally of the value of nine
shillings and four pence sterling, or somewhat more that two dollars.
The silver ducat is of about half this value.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ducatoon</ent>⟦br⟧
